wherevpon he taking occaſion to performe his damnable pretence, walked vp and downe about the houſe, as one ye had ſome matter of importance, or ſome greate miſchiefe hammering in his head. The gentlewoman perceyuing it (for that his countenance argued, he was not content) ſhe ſent one of hir maydes to know, if any of hyr houſe had offended him, or that he lacked his deſire in any thing. This mayde doyng hir miſtreſſe meſſage, the Fatherly Frier, or rather Helliſh fiende, toke hir (in ſigne of curteſie) by the hande, and leading hir aſide into a corner of the Court, he cut hir throate. In the meane while there arriued a Tenaunt of the gentlemans that brought him rent, who hū
